<p class="eyebrow">Support / Softphone / Zoiper</p>
<h1>Configure Zoiper for VoiceTel.</h1>
<p class="lede">Zoiper 5 across all platforms accepts standard SIP account credentials. The free tier covers SIP-over-UDP, which is what VoiceTel SIP trunks use.</p>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Steps (Zoiper 5 desktop)</h2>
	<ol>
		<li>Open Zoiper → <strong>Settings → Accounts → Add account</strong>.</li>
		<li>Choose <strong>SIP</strong> account type, click <strong>Yes</strong> when asked if you have an account.</li>
		<li>Enter your VoiceTel SIP credentials:
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Username:</strong> SIP username from VoiceTel onboarding</li>
				<li><strong>Password:</strong> SIP password from onboarding</li>
				<li><strong>Domain / Host:</strong> SIP server host (shown in the customer portal)</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Click <strong>Next</strong>. Zoiper auto-detects the registration server and authentication settings.</li>
		<li>If auto-detection fails, click <strong>Skip</strong> and configure the account manually:
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Domain:</strong> the SIP server host shown in your customer portal</li>
				<li><strong>Outbound proxy:</strong> same as Domain</li>
				<li><strong>Auth username:</strong> same as Username</li>
				<li><strong>Use outbound proxy:</strong> Yes</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Open the new account's <strong>Network</strong> sub-tab:
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Transport:</strong> UDP</li>
				<li><strong>Use STUN:</strong> off — leave disabled</li>
				<li><strong>Registration interval:</strong> 60</li>
			</ul>
		</li>
		<li>Open <strong>Audio codecs</strong>. Enable PCMU and PCMA; disable everything else unless onboarding confirmed support.</li>
		<li>Click <strong>Save</strong>. Status indicator at the bottom should turn green.</li>
	</ol>
</section>

<section class="section-block">
	<h2>Zoiper mobile</h2>
	<p>Same flow on iOS / Android: <strong>Add account → Manual configuration → SIP</strong>. Enter Domain, Username, Password. Set Transport to UDP, disable STUN, set Registration to 60.</p>
</section>

